        "title": "feat: identify diarized speakers",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- identify diarized YouTube speakers using verified timestamp anchors, reusable profiles, transcript-hash-guarded mappings, and OpenAI GPT-5.5 context inference\n- add atomic `--remember-speakers` config persistence while retaining generic labels below the confidence threshold\n- harden HTML extraction and DNS-pinned fetches, and preserve MiniMax M3 metadata under the seven-day dependency policy\n\n## Validation\n\n- `pnpm -s check`\n- 423 test files passed, 27 skipped\n- 2,215 tests passed, 41 skipped\n- structured autoreview clean with no accepted/actionable findings\n- replayed against ElevenLabs Scribe v2 output for Modern Wisdom episodes 1108 and 1099; corrected a stale four-person benchmark mapping while retaining an unverified embedded speaker as generic\n\n## Safety\n\n- raw diarization cache remains generic; identity-aware extract cache keys prevent cross-profile reuse\n- remembered mappings apply only to exact transcript SHA-256 hashes\n- config writes reject symlinks, use an exclusive lock and atomic rename, and preserve unknown settings\n",
